{
  "stem": "9899.3",
  "chunk_idx": 0,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So they discovered this hiding place of all those-- that group of Jews.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And instead of making a large hole for them to come out easily, their diabolical plan was to make it as small as possible to make it very difficult for them.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And so they pulled out each head that appeared by the hair, taking off their skin and the hair together of every man, woman, and child that came out.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "It was a horrible sight.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "It was so close to where we were standing and not being able to do anything.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "My mother left the house.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "She wanted to see if there was a way of helping them.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "But they were all put-- they were like 80 of them, more or less, with little children.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Men, women, women that were pregnant, women that had babies in their arms.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "Each and every one of the adults were put against the wall, and each baby that was not able to walk was taken by the feet and hit against the wall, like you would do with a fly--",
      "word_count": 38
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Swatter, until they were all dead.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "They were shot right then and there.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "One of the women had a little bundle in her arms, and she saw my mother, so she kicked the bundle towards her.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But the German saw it, and before my mother could move, he grabbed the bundle.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "He took the little baby that must have been maybe a week old and ripped it apart by the legs in half.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Such cruelty.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Such inhuman-- [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] Such inhumanity from one person to another.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "It is unfathomable.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "I cannot today believe that a person is able to perform this cruel act on another human being.",
      "word_count": 18
    }
  ],
